                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12892457" author="jdcryans" created="Mon, 26 Jul 2010 20:52:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d vote to instead remove the need to have a master to run the shell. This has blocked me quite a few times.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12892463" author="nspiegelberg" created="Mon, 26 Jul 2010 21:04:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;however, there&apos;s also the subtle problem of the ZK CLI within the HBase shell requiring ruby syntax, where all the ZK documentation uses it&apos;s own CLI syntax.  I think it&apos;s useful in both places, but I think you should have the option to use the ZK CLI in the same manner that it&apos;s documented.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12892949" author="stack" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2010 21:51:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added.  No harm having it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017539" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:43:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
